ZH: 改弦易辙，是指事情发展出现问题时需要及时调整方法。
EN: "改弦易辙" means adjusting your approach when encountering obstacles in the development of a situation.

ZH: 面对困难，我们要勇于改弦易辙，不要固守旧有的方法。
EN: When facing difficulties, we should bravely change our approach and not stick to old methods.

ZH: 在工作中，改弦易辙能够帮助我们更快地应对变化。
EN: Changing our approach can help us adapt to changes more quickly in our work.

ZH: 领导者要有改弦易辙的能力，才能应对复杂的情况。
EN: Leaders need to have the ability to change their approach in order to deal with complicated situations.

ZH: 在学习中，改弦易辙可以帮助我们找到解决问题的新途径。
EN: Changing our approach in learning can help us find new ways to solve problems.

ZH: 遇到困难时，改弦易辙是破解难题的有效方法。
EN: When facing difficulties, changing our approach is an effective way to solve problems.

ZH: 知错就改，改弦易辙，才能不断进步。
EN: We can only make progress by admitting mistakes and changing our approach.

ZH: 当前的局势已经发生变化，我们要及时改弦易辙。
EN: The current situation has changed, so we need to adjust our approach promptly.

ZH: 做事要灵活变通，有改弦易辙的能力。
EN: We need to be flexible and have the ability to change our approach when doing things.

ZH: 拒绝改弦易辙只会让问题变得更加复杂。
EN: Refusing to change our approach will only make the problem more complicated.

ZH: 在生活中，改弦易辙可以帮助我们摆脱困境。
EN: Changing our approach in life can help us get out of difficulties.

ZH: 面对困难，要果断改弦易辙，不要固步自封。
EN: Faced with difficulties, we should decisively change our approach and not be stuck in old ways.

ZH: 他是一个能够随机应变、改弦易辙的领导者。
EN: He is a leader who can adapt and change his approach easily.

ZH: 在创新过程中，改弦易辙是非常重要的。
EN: Changing our approach is crucial in the process of innovation.

ZH: 我们需要及时调整策略，改弦易辙，以应对市场竞争。
EN: We need to adjust our strategy promptly and change our approach to deal with market competition.

